(6, 'Apple and Android phones hacked by Italian spyware, Google says', 10, 'An Italian company\'s hacking tools were used to spy on Apple and Android smartphones in Italy and Kazakhstan, Alphabet\'s Google said in a report on Thursday.', 1, 2, '<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_87D7A827-3D24-6885-9DBE-91752CD15866\">Milan-based RCS Lab, whose website claims European law enforcement agencies as clients, developed tools to spy on private messages and contacts of the targeted devices, the report said.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_2651C168-D627-52A4-0CE8-91752CD4953E\">Google&nbsp;(<span class=\"inlink_chart\"><a class=\"inlink\" href=\"https://money.cnn.com/quote/quote.html?symb=GOOG&amp;source=story_quote_link\">GOOG</a></span>)\'s findings on RCS Lab come as European and American regulators weigh potential new rules over the sale and import of spyware.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_3484F72A-1279-9532-F1E7-9175B1BD523F\">\"These vendors are enabling the proliferation of dangerous hacking tools and arming governments that would not be able to develop these capabilities in-house,\" Google said.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_8E05B9CB-E6F3-D070-3A64-9175B325876D\">Apple&nbsp;(<span class=\"inlink_chart\"><a class=\"inlink\" href=\"https://money.cnn.com/quote/quote.html?symb=AAPL&amp;source=story_quote_link\">AAPL</a></span>)&nbsp;and the governments of Italy and Kazakhstan did not immediately respond to requests for comment.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__read-all\">\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_2AC3B9A0-5F82-C43A-0E68-9175B32E054C\">RCS Lab said its products and services comply with European rules and help law enforcement agencies investigate crimes.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_3B2BD352-EBAE-6D17-8043-9175B3311B53\">\"RCS Lab personnel are not exposed, nor participate in any activities conducted by the relevant customers,\" it told Reuters in an email, adding that it condemned any abuse of its products.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_F0E15744-BB13-91EA-D116-9175CBB7B6EE\">Google said it had taken steps to protect users of its Android operating system and alerted them about the spyware.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_6D0AF597-E45E-E486-48DE-9175CD3830A1\">The global industry making spyware for governments has been growing, with more and more companies developing interception tools for law enforcement organizations. Anti-surveillance activists accuse them of aiding governments that in some cases are using such tools to crack down on human rights and civil rights.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_E80DA5EB-A089-D6A7-8FA9-9175EF956010\">The industry came under a global spotlight when the Israeli surveillance firm NSO\'s Pegasus spyware was in recent years found to have been used by multiple governments to spy on journalists, activists, and dissidents.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_2B2E5969-026E-0E91-2ECE-9175F2A82FD5\">While RCS Lab\'s tool may not be as stealthy as Pegasus, it can still read messages and view passwords, said Bill Marczak, a security researcher with digital watchdog Citizen Lab.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_D5C2FA1E-4DB6-9935-00D7-9175F2AAF659\">\"This shows that even though these devices are ubiquitous, there\'s still a long way to go in securing them against these powerful attacks,\" he added.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_97FA9406-A292-8CFC-4051-9175F2AC38EB\">On its website, RCS Lab describes itself as a maker of \"lawful interception\" technologies and services including voice, data collection and \"tracking systems.\" It says it handles 10,000 intercepted targets daily in Europe alone.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_A123AF8A-333F-0A2B-6230-9175F2AF3CC7\">Google researchers found RCS Lab had previously collaborated with the controversial, defunct Italian spy firm Hacking Team, which had similarly created surveillance software for foreign governments to tap into phones and computers.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_DBC14093-CDD4-52B8-F903-9175F2B06262\">Hacking Team went bust after it became a victim of a major hack in 2015 that led to a disclosure of numerous internal documents.</div>\r\n<div class=\"zn-body__paragraph\" data-paragraph-id=\"paragraph_A84945F9-742A-122C-16CB-9175F2B24E6A\">In some cases, Google said it believed hackers using RCS spyware worked with the target\'s internet service provider, which suggests they had ties to government-backed actors, said Billy Leonard, a senior researcher at Google.</div>\r\n</div>', '24. 6. 2022 | 19:41', 1, 158),
(7, 'Apple’s AR / VR headset could release in January, analyst predicts', 12, 'Apple’s long-rumored mixed reality headset, which will reportedly offer a combination of augmented and virtual reality experiences, will “likely release” in January 2023, according to respected Apple analyst Ming-Chi Kuo. In a new analyst note seen by 9to5Mac, Kuo notes that the headset is “the most complicated product Apple has ever designed” but that its release could help fuel “rapid growth” in the market for head-mounted displays.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"A1EqKx\">This is far from the first time Kuo has predicted when Apple&rsquo;s headset could release, but previous predictions have had far wider release windows. Last year he said we might see the headset released&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/3/7/22318239/apple-mixed-reality-headset-2022-analyst-kuo\">at some point in 2022</a>&nbsp;(which now seems unlikely), and just this month he predicted that a release could come at some point in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://9to5mac.com/2022/06/07/apple-mixed-reality-headset-coming-q2-2023/\">second quarter of next year</a>. This doesn&rsquo;t guarantee a January announcement (Apple&rsquo;s plans could change, or Kuo&rsquo;s supply chain sources could be wrong), but listing a specific month is a strong show of confidence from the analyst.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656093177_4466_1003770\" data-cdata=\"{&quot;asset_id&quot;:22280992,&quot;ratio&quot;:&quot;*&quot;}\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6ZfTqVacGv40Al57umrlxzi_sh0=/0x0:1860x981/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wKckjpcYiggqSKorHH470EvydFA=/0x0:1860x981/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/GbBD_jMkr32Yp72-QimVbUBt-v0=/0x0:1860x981/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/oTIwj5EGBtOiUkE6lN-fA3CMXLs=/0x0:1860x981/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ezQs3870jRhRObKpEFn9SUgz8b4=/0x0:1860x981/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iHYs6YsGv9dr1EiTysBGZdb0Gf4=/0x0:1860x981/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RNe5GHkrk4Rn7sIi9TonOHWp3TI=/0x0:1860x981/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8Pm1ZRSsL_HLV0H_IzqW6xXFE6w=/0x0:1860x981/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NjUquFU6StS7w3J8pbKKD6QFKKE=/0x0:1860x981/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tH4g1KkxXqO7Xy7Bdp3avCq-0Jg=/0x0:1860x981/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kpNUvWqBftpuyB3PtiOQTvFaQ5Y=/0x0:1860x981/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Fvv50-LEUZ0OLW96NRLW_XuxNxc=/0x0:1860x981/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/oCn5hi8OCxjS_4VK-TNwKCHvTMg=/0x0:1860x981/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Un5pZJszNfTTd4pzbvhd1T8MUnA=/0x0:1860x981/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QbgHgdBvAOgE0hfssKwpHBVycAQ=/0x0:1860x981/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7GU89iAK2-6BfXJDxnRI8hmcSeQ=/0x0:1860x981/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/mt1rSoyRVxhS5WEZUSglZ859g4Y=/0x0:1860x981/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FjfCs7mE3QU7kOFwrjKOephoXOs=/0x0:1860x981/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XpeVO3KGoBzTWkWuEuSP8nHdgdQ=/0x0:1860x981/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1860x981):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/22280992/3b786602_c662_4696_b68c_21f89e4a4e95.jpg 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"1860\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>Apple&rsquo;s headset could reportedly look like this.</em></figcaption>\r\n<span class=\"e-image__meta\">&nbsp;<cite>Image:&nbsp;<a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://www.theinformation.com/articles/new-apple-mixed-reality-headset-details-swappable-headbands-eye-tracking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>The Information</em></a></cite></span></figure>\r\n<p id=\"hCsPfc\">It also coincides with a lot of reported activity around the headset at Apple. The company&rsquo;s board of directors reportedly&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/19/23131051/apple-vr-ar-headset-prototype-board-of-directors-demo\">tried out the headset in early May</a>, mentions of the headset&rsquo;s RealityOS software are&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22925038/apple-realityos-augmented-reality-headset-operating-system-rumors\">cropping up in Apple&rsquo;s code</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/30/23147213/realityos-os-ros-trademark-apple-virtual-augmented-reality-headset\">appearing in trademark applications</a>, and Apple CEO Tim Cook&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/22/23178569/apple-ar-headset-tim-cook-tease\">recently teased</a>&nbsp;upcoming augmented reality announcements.</p>\r\n<p id=\"7Ol09k\">Numerous reports over the years have attempted to shed light on Apple&rsquo;s elusive headset. It will reportedly work as a standalone device rather than needing to be tethered to a computer, and it could have as many as 14 cameras to track its movement, according to a recent&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/20/23133038/apple-mixed-virtual-augmented-reality-ar-vr-headset-self-contained-device\">report in&nbsp;<em>The Information</em></a><em>.&nbsp;</em>Internally, it&rsquo;ll reportedly have a processor with a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/11/26/22802981/apple-ar-headset-m1-processor-release-date-specs\">similar amount of processing power to M1 chips</a>&nbsp;found in recent Macs, though when it comes to power it&rsquo;s unclear whether its battery will be wearable on the user&rsquo;s body, or built into the headset itself.</p>\r\n<p id=\"cReBy2\">While Kuo predicts that Apple is about to make a big splash in the mixed reality headset space, he expects its main competitor Meta to take a step back,&nbsp;<em>9to5Mac&nbsp;</em>reports. Kuo expects the company formerly known as Facebook to cut back its near term investment in VR hardware to focus on its advertising business. That&rsquo;s in spite of Meta recently showing off a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/20/23172503/mark-zuckerberg-meta-vr-headset-prototype-reveal-butterscotch-sunburst-holocake-mirror-lake\">host of VR headset prototypes</a>&nbsp;it&rsquo;s working on.</p>', '24. 6. 2022 | 20:12', 1, 75),
(9, 'Google’s Pixel 5 was the last of its kind', 67, 'From time to time, I’ll grab a random device out of the Verge reviews closet and spend a week or two with it. It’s mostly out of random curiosity and for the sake of comparing “old” products against the latest and greatest. Most recently, I was drawn to Google’s Pixel 5. So I gave it a factory reset, updated the phone to Android 12, and have been using it as my daily driver for the past several days.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"HUweC8\">The experience has been fantastic. I&rsquo;ve got very large hands &mdash; an iPhone 13 Pro Max doesn&rsquo;t look out of place in them &mdash; and I prefer large screens, so I don&rsquo;t think I could fully switch over to the Pixel 5. But it&rsquo;s such a good &ldquo;small&rdquo; phone (by 2022 standards) that I&rsquo;ve certainly been tempted. The Pixel 5 makes it easy to do anything I need one-handed. Its midrange processor performs better than ever on Android 12, and this phone still looks unique next to the competition.</p>\r\n<p id=\"fheWhb\">Above all else, I&rsquo;ve come away disappointed that Google gave up on the Pixel 5&rsquo;s style and size after just one year. The smallest phone in the company&rsquo;s lineup is currently the Pixel 5a, which has a 6.3-inch display. To its credit, Google is shrinking things down slightly with the upcoming 6A. But with the A-series models, you&rsquo;re&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/12/23067680/google-pixel-6a-phone-camera-tensor\">giving up niceties</a>&nbsp;like the 90Hz display and wireless charging. In those ways, the Pixel 5 might be the last of its kind in Google&rsquo;s lineup. So much for the even bezels, too.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656175219_2287_1385330\" data-cdata=\"{\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4i7A_7PO3DMP1jPMyJj3z4XupAk=/0x0:2614x1042/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FPVbSlspGXX9JM0r31HUpRwbSJw=/0x0:2614x1042/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/N8N7f55PEPT6kqCKof1JRHJkf0I=/0x0:2614x1042/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tJeYEKemXsmU_djXMMYGxa-vdsE=/0x0:2614x1042/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/340W358Z9ETlVym6zgY6aH-2uqI=/0x0:2614x1042/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2vPcgAwDnsE1OdSNX3qZfG-MUHc=/0x0:2614x1042/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FUKtryuEJdc2sPtTs6U6n0MqRXs=/0x0:2614x1042/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sGt4G8jnIqt9vdlyNvfppCwKimY=/0x0:2614x1042/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CeAub38lIjVf_qeuKhSGIx4ZDTo=/0x0:2614x1042/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/drLyoKIIYh_3FsL0JuITn5pB7C4=/0x0:2614x1042/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Sc-168hOxh4dhjks74pOfs7Qmdo=/0x0:2614x1042/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KiE0lRHiE6digkPVY3k3L8QXR4Y=/0x0:2614x1042/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6iJFb6BqTAO2sDbcnjrt5Mxm_mo=/0x0:2614x1042/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nujX7K9VhWVj-Xuo4BkQPpLi_G8=/0x0:2614x1042/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/t98LQZ4TlSyd946pAiQ60Pe4nsA=/0x0:2614x1042/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Ve1yApy7TXo60Fee5Fv2GED78g8=/0x0:2614x1042/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/DrpNLanOipEXc6ogQcQebGKQdzw=/0x0:2614x1042/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IculV_BwtSa7u7Spxz_VpBwjaXc=/0x0:2614x1042/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Be-iPSsj2GcO4rJRZhhtFge2MMY=/0x0:2614x1042/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2614x1042):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649876/Screen_Shot_2022_06_24_at_1.10.33_PM.png 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"2614\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>The Pixel 5 is smaller than both the Pixel 5A and 6A &mdash; with more premium hardware to boot.</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"nXHBjp\">I now find myself wishing that Google would keep the 5 around as an &ldquo;iPhone SE&rdquo;-style product that gets brought up to speed with hardware upgrades every couple years &mdash; without losing what makes it good. Let&rsquo;s cover some of the Pixel 5&rsquo;s strengths.</p>\r\n<p id=\"hBxf9T\"><strong>Design and materials:&nbsp;</strong>The Pixel 5&rsquo;s 6-inch OLED display is surrounded by thin, symmetrical bezels that go a long way in making the phone comfortable and usable in one hand. And the textured &ldquo;bio resin&rdquo; coating on the 5&rsquo;s body results in a unique feel and reassuring grip when you&rsquo;re holding it throughout the day. The volume rocker shares this texture, while the power button is glossy metal &mdash; making it easy to distinguish between the two by touch. Owing to its feel and palm-able size, the Pixel 5 is one of those phones that can go caseless without causing much consternation.</p>\r\n<p id=\"pGa1ma\">Before Google went all in on the common &ldquo;glass sandwich&rdquo; design with the Pixel 6 and 6 Pro, previous models in the series often used distinctive materials and textures that helped the phones stand out. With the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2017/10/17/16486108/google-pixel-2-xl-review-android-phone-camera\">Pixel 2</a>, it was the almost-coarse rear shell of the black model. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/10/21/20923660/google-pixel-4-xl-review-camera-radar-face-unlock-90hz-display-telephoto\">Pixel 4</a>&nbsp;had grippy side rails. But after the 5&rsquo;s bio resin &mdash; I&rsquo;m still a big fan of the Sorta Sage green colorway with this finish &mdash; Google opted for a more basic in-hand feel with last year&rsquo;s flagships.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656175219_5401_1385331\" data-cdata=\"{\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/41A95pzEQjotpCZxse7mzu7YhMo=/0x0:2040x1360/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Z35sqWZPp6g5yGAtRlMr9QjZVdI=/0x0:2040x1360/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UqCtR5QEvAM8Fo8dgDaa95IyoHs=/0x0:2040x1360/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-oM8xFyEQxeudXYRo62gyaAZLEQ=/0x0:2040x1360/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-GA049Ug0BjakuIk6sBzMj8eFRc=/0x0:2040x1360/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zecLih1BJK6Cg1JyX6aTXG0qyjQ=/0x0:2040x1360/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OoKIHC9DEzLoXPKQeabm2QWXVoo=/0x0:2040x1360/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/l5U0NRHFvjtWRblbXvrerFFpTGo=/0x0:2040x1360/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tPbyF9lng1LMs2aaL6Jqd1er9Z8=/0x0:2040x1360/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3fAldoo0BX9z2b8wtBY-BCuxn6U=/0x0:2040x1360/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/AfapgJyJCjQ2DVSNv-LBEFdq5as=/0x0:2040x1360/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nSJ5uvHVnmHRkCRTBMAnPOD_QLM=/0x0:2040x1360/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/927oytaesu8a68JrKAyL9TUKS4Y=/0x0:2040x1360/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nvfCzK3ks52PzEwU8gatny5z8gA=/0x0:2040x1360/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/eN7UNHelPZD-lkiVShfUOyta6ps=/0x0:2040x1360/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1G_ofBLS_nJfNY_SQ1p5ZaF4_9c=/0x0:2040x1360/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qpXjtvmY8Zo4YiWvCT1z_JDgdaE=/0x0:2040x1360/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/azuwLZtbSKIPG0On1DXz0e1OyOs=/0x0:2040x1360/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1MWMfHsob2ebRTml_m2Z4_aVBqk=/0x0:2040x1360/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/21955669/akrales_201012_4137_0132.0.jpg 1920w\" alt=\"The power button is plain instead of having a pop of color\" data-upload-width=\"2040\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>The Pixel 5&rsquo;s bio resin finish makes for a unique in-hand feel.</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"L41mFb\"><strong>A better screen:</strong>&nbsp;The Pixel 6&rsquo;s OLED panel might seem perfectly fine based on first impressions. But in all honesty, it&rsquo;s mediocre. There are plenty of threads on Reddit complaining about uniformity issues, an unsightly green tint at lower brightness levels, and other imperfections. The Pixel 6 Pro&rsquo;s gorgeous LPTO panel exhibits none of these problems, so it&rsquo;s clear that Google settled for less as part of reaching the 6&rsquo;s $599 price.</p>\r\n<p id=\"cyYSRo\">Even the Pixel 5&rsquo;s screen seems of a slightly higher quality to me than the 6 that replaced it. They&rsquo;re both 90Hz displays, but the 5&rsquo;s white point, uniformity, and overall image are just a bit nicer to my eyes. This can sometimes come down to variance between individual units, but I hope to see better from the Pixel 7.</p>\r\n<p id=\"FKkvDd\"><strong>Pixel Imprint rear fingerprint sensor:&nbsp;</strong>I&rsquo;m still let down that phone makers decided in unison to relocate the fingerprint reader from the back of the phone, where your index finger often naturally rests while holding it, to underneath the display. Google&rsquo;s Pixel Imprint scanners were perhaps the fastest and most consistent in the entire Android ecosystem, and, well, let&rsquo;s just say the in-screen sensor on the Pixel 6 and 6 Pro has never matched it &mdash; even after Google improved the performance through software updates.</p>\r\n<p id=\"ATTu3r\"><strong>Consistent camera performance:&nbsp;</strong>Google spent several years optimizing its computational photography for the 12-megapixel main camera shared by the Pixel 5 and its predecessors. And while it lacks the dynamic range of the Pixel 6 / 6 Pro and doesn&rsquo;t offer features like Real Tone or Magic Eraser, the Pixel 5 is a consistent shooter. You know what you&rsquo;re going to get, which can&rsquo;t always be said of the Pixel 6 line. I don&rsquo;t love the unpleasant-looking background blur you sometimes get from the 6&rsquo;s larger sensor, but this is something Google will no doubt improve.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656175219_1990_1385332\" data-cdata=\"{\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3StgsYrUKl9IN7Um2x65AiSDTRw=/0x0:1920x1080/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/aM3Idg5sDvntrkA6cn5s7WUUSqw=/0x0:1920x1080/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BxCVF11t6oHrMBSpTaYo_eJKrsc=/0x0:1920x1080/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qe7bE7oErkH8easywEt8bofQ4NY=/0x0:1920x1080/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dT_b2FAXMhCXqtYwE3Qk_os3h2Y=/0x0:1920x1080/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vdLpneaQ-rmoJ_Qy7UFtCdkTpEk=/0x0:1920x1080/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/p2z1kuBPr1HQmA_ht1jQaWRjB64=/0x0:1920x1080/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sQPwaicyheIoXoRo0MImxuzy0W0=/0x0:1920x1080/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2vg7p_7ZyAlPp3FfS_59ix17BtQ=/0x0:1920x1080/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/AUAl-nKwBTMNkpq9l9Gi7VL62xk=/0x0:1920x1080/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UMlapryHa5K0JJszxKuP5csGzV0=/0x0:1920x1080/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bTMaqKzVlRRIvhvOlkP3SLntA-c=/0x0:1920x1080/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/rd6eKqkUIB8D5t2P54UbfpL-diI=/0x0:1920x1080/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Oy1QThf71fmgrQKOq_QDGLl2hes=/0x0:1920x1080/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CFVXnszD51zzsrF96XTglHjd5Rg=/0x0:1920x1080/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1j8hag144V6ULUvb_fpvl7Cq0ck=/0x0:1920x1080/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kCRGqLcatOeRb-z576COZ77IQeY=/0x0:1920x1080/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HgMbo4dIRxL2XpOKkYmfnd1dt6w=/0x0:1920x1080/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Dh0Z-0ajyukO8r5LDb4-NWHQO9M=/0x0:1920x1080/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1920x1080):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23649991/pixel6a.jpeg 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"1920\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>The Pixel 6A will soon be Google&rsquo;s smallest phone.</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<h2 id=\"IeGpzt\">THE PIXEL 5 ISN&rsquo;T PERFECT</h2>\r\n<p id=\"flI4D9\">Although I&rsquo;m mostly satisfied with the smooth performance and general responsiveness of the Pixel 5 on Android 12, there are still occasions where the midrange Snapdragon 765G processor hits a wall and gets bogged down. Snap a photo, and the frustrating delay while the phone processes the shot remains present. The 5 can also get hung up if you get overly ambitious with multitasking.</p>\r\n<p id=\"DJEcon\">While I&rsquo;m sold on the Pixel 5&rsquo;s look and feel, Google&rsquo;s hardware quality assurance isn&rsquo;t always the best. Many units have&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/2020/11/04/pixel-5-owners-report-gaps-between-phones-display-and-frame/\">a slight gap between the display and body</a>. After the phone&rsquo;s release, the company&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/11/4/21549778/google-pixel-5-display-gap-issue-normal-design\">said the gap wasn&rsquo;t anything to worry about</a>&nbsp;&mdash; but it&rsquo;s exactly the sort of minor detail that I find annoying.</p>\r\n<p id=\"UzBRcU\">And then there&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/GooglePixel/comments/jo9emc/pixel_5_speakers_are_really_that_bad/\">that dreadful under-screen speaker</a>, which still sounds tinny in most cases even after Google tried to improve it with an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/12/7/22158452/google-pixel-december-feature-drop-features\">&ldquo;adaptive sound&rdquo; setting</a>. Those symmetrical bezels didn&rsquo;t come without tradeoffs.</p>\r\n<p id=\"dQeiOq\">But even with those downsides factored in, there&rsquo;s still something special about this phone. I&rsquo;ve come close to buying one from Woot, which is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?xcust=___vg__p_22945836__t_w__r_theverge.com/tech__d_D&amp;id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https://electronics.woot.com/offers/new-google-pixel-5-w-5g-128gb-fully-unlocked?ref=w_cnt_lnd_cat_elec_2_21&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/25/23181795/google-pixel-5-android-12-iphone-se\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" data-cdata=\"{\">selling new, unopened Pixel 5s for $450</a>. Apparently Google must&rsquo;ve stumbled across some extra inventory in a warehouse somewhere. With Apple&rsquo;s mini iPhone rumored to be cut from the upcoming iPhone 14 lineup, it seems small phones are on the way out (again). That makes this a tempting moment to buy. The only asterisk to consider in Google&rsquo;s case is that software support for the Pixel 5 will end in October 2023.</p>\r\n<p id=\"dlASHB\">But maybe by then, Google will reintroduce a small Pixel that doesn&rsquo;t skimp on hardware features and doesn&rsquo;t so blandly take after its larger siblings.</p>', '25. 6. 2022 | 19:01', 1, 116),
(10, 'Here’s Google’s letter saying employees can relocate to states with abortion rights', 68, 'In the wake of the Supreme Court’s decision on Friday to overturn Roe v. Wade, Google’s chief people officer Fiona Cicconi sent a staff-wide email to employees informing them of Google’s response to the ruling. Among other things, the email highlights that Googlers can “apply for relocation without justification” and that people in charge of the relocation process “will be aware of the situation” in assessing their requests. In an email last August reported by Bloomberg, Google told employees that of 10,000 requests over the prior few months to work remotely or relocate, 85 percent were approved.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"JVX3gw\">The Supreme Court&rsquo;s ruling does not make abortion illegal throughout the US &mdash; instead, it leaves the decision to individual state governments. A number of states have&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2022/06/24/abortion-state-laws-criminalization-roe/\">immediately restricted abortion rights</a>, including Louisiana, Missouri, and Kentucky. Other states, including California, where Google is headquartered, have&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/23065585/democrats-roe-abortion-protection-law-legislature\">vowed to protect abortion rights</a>&nbsp;within their borders.</p>\r\n<p id=\"K0wxUH\">Here&rsquo;s the letter in full:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p id=\"D0nkdx\">Hi everyone,</p>\r\n<p id=\"byWEYG\">This morning the US Supreme Court issued a ruling in<em>&nbsp;Dobbs v. Jackson Women&rsquo;s Health Organization</em>&nbsp;that rolls back&nbsp;<em>Roe v. Wade</em>.</p>\r\n<p id=\"GReGk5\">This is a profound change for the country that deeply affects so many of us, especially women. Everyone will respond in their own way, whether that&rsquo;s wanting space and time to process, speaking up, volunteering outside of work, not wanting to discuss it at all, or something else entirely. Please be mindful of what your co-workers may be feeling and, as always, treat each other with respect.</p>\r\n<p id=\"d8EZRK\">Equity is extraordinarily important to us as a company, and we share concerns about the impact this ruling will have on people&rsquo;s health, lives, and careers. We will keep working to make information on reproductive healthcare accessible across our products and continue our work to protect user privacy.</p>\r\n<p id=\"8ahzT8\">To support Googlers and their dependents, our US benefits plan and health insurance covers out-of-state medical procedures that are not available where an employee lives and works. Googlers can also apply for relocation without justification, and those overseeing this process will be aware of the situation. If you need additional support, please connect 1:1 with a People Consultant via [link to internal tool redacted].</p>\r\n<p id=\"wiYWBq\">We will be arranging support sessions for Googlers in the US in the coming days. These will be posted to Googler News.</p>\r\n<p id=\"t2a8LO\">Please don&rsquo;t hesitate to lean on your Google community in the days ahead and continue to take good care of yourselves and each other.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p id=\"TNsdyw\"><em>The Verge</em>&nbsp;has reached out to Google to clarify whether anything about the relocation policy has changed specifically due to the Supreme Court&rsquo;s decision. We will update this story if there are any additional details.</p>', '25. 6. 2022 | 19:38', 1, 13),
(12, 'Samsung’s monstrous 55-inch Odyssey Ark monitor could go on sale in August', 70, 'Samsung is getting ready to release its massive 55-inch curved Odyssey Ark monitor in August, according to a report from Korean outlet ETNews (via SamMobile). The monitor, which was announced in January at CES, has reportedly gone through a few certification programs that have to be done before it can go on sale.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"cr8Hsj\">Details about this monitor are still scant. The company has said that it&rsquo;ll have a 16:9 4K panel and that the stand will support pivot, tilt, and rotation. It also announced that it would come out in the second half of 2022 (which the reported August window falls squarely in). But let&rsquo;s be honest, when you show up with a monitor that promises to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/qbking77/status/1478555909068505088\">physically tower over you</a>&nbsp;while you&rsquo;re using it, people will pay attention even if you don&rsquo;t announce the price or refresh rate.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656175671_7209_1366793\" data-cdata=\"{&quot;asset_id&quot;:23146140,&quot;ratio&quot;:&quot;*&quot;}\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/x80Qkwhuzz3xZ_sOEn9iohNyoic=/0x0:4000x2250/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/50HHavF3KPkPBGM6an1jni_pEYQ=/0x0:4000x2250/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VtFXViHPrN_8pVUktdVtgDL-I7A=/0x0:4000x2250/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_RJ7GecSUvFTiTb-dirVuK5KZu8=/0x0:4000x2250/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/WAseuWsJxgIcppMtjiuL-fu3hNY=/0x0:4000x2250/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/e4XFTIk1F89nH8eqV1v8vHxHMSk=/0x0:4000x2250/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9V6-_-XEnJdyHXKsupb0s7-ctgE=/0x0:4000x2250/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/W1JPiSQg8sxw-E1kV74ChA6JIqg=/0x0:4000x2250/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NdWxTE4aVgzuProgpAy3actUWjY=/0x0:4000x2250/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/J7jdX9MS_oSI5Y_1jKpD04qwmEo=/0x0:4000x2250/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xuDVF9S_uUUP6YhWON_i8bgrVY0=/0x0:4000x2250/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yt4NlV2FTFjcecVp1xbT5oYpqcQ=/0x0:4000x2250/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3vL5JpodCI31TFkslj3XHZyyLHk=/0x0:4000x2250/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9n83-N74D9xzJjZULQex6bK1qac=/0x0:4000x2250/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/r4a18WIxTpmERNetqS1_tFDDYvQ=/0x0:4000x2250/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gUKr3eeSUBH5PGlZYo3EVrZqo4k=/0x0:4000x2250/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/h2pzScUm1cK8CQivFZmnRUpPdCY=/0x0:4000x2250/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IbpwSizTuNppIEdF_8ZygVPoFeU=/0x0:4000x2250/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/M6Y2JAyNYI4Hdq4vbnJ2r-8F1Nw=/0x0:4000x2250/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:4000x2250):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23146140/Odyssey_Ark_above.jpg 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"4000\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>Samsung says the dial is for managing &ldquo;lighting and the interface.&rdquo; Because buttons on the back would be very hard to reach.</em></figcaption>\r\n<span class=\"e-image__meta\">&nbsp;<cite>Image: Samsung</cite></span></figure>\r\n<p id=\"6I7cjS\">Many of us here at&nbsp;<em>The Verge</em>&nbsp;are very excited for this monitor &mdash; when it came time to hand out awards for CES 2022, we&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22870203/ces-2022-best-of-gadgets-concepts-tech\">gave it Best in Show</a>. But as with many CES announcements, as the months wear on, it can be hard to remember anything from the flood of gadgets and tech; did Samsung&nbsp;<em>really</em>&nbsp;announce an extremely curved, extremely large monitor that can stretch over and around you, or was that just a fever dream? Rumors that it could actually be coming out relatively soon prove that it was, in fact, actually announced and reminds us that we are looking forward to it.</p>\r\n<p id=\"4mr2tf\">One thing that adds a bit of credence to the report is that Samsung has successfully released other monitors that it announced around CES this year. The decidedly less ambitious (but very cute) M8 monitor has&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/3/28/22999709/samsung-m8-4k-32-inch-smart-monitor-features-price-airplay-tv-apple-studio-display-comparison\">already started hitting store shelves</a>, as has a smaller (read: reasonably sized) curved gaming monitor,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/23/23137590/samsung-odyssey-neo-g8-gaming-monitor-price-release-date-specs-preorder\">the Odyssey Neo G8</a>. While that&rsquo;s obviously not proof that the Ark is up next, it is good to see that Samsung has a track record of shipping its CES monitors this year.</p>', '25. 6. 2022 | 19:44', 1, 5);
INSERT INTO `article` (`id`, `title`, `title_image_id`, `perex`, `author_id`, `category_id`, `content`, `date_added`, `is_published`, `views`) VALUES
(13, 'Graphics Card Prices are Finally Coming Down', 71, 'PC builders, rejoice: After years of a shortage causing painfully high costs, graphics cards are finally returning to slightly more affordable prices.', 1, 2, '<p>According to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.digitaltrends.com/computing/amd-and-nvidia-gpus-now-selling-close-to-msrp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><u>a report by Digital Trends</u></a>, the prices of both AMD and Nvidia graphics cards are on their way down. Newer cards are becoming notably cheaper, with Nvidia\'s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ign.com/tech/nvidia-geforce-rtx-3090-ti\">RTX 3090 Ti</a>&nbsp;now at 16% under MSRP and AMD\'s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ign.com/tech/amd-radeon-rx-6950-xt\">RX 6950 XT</a>&nbsp;at 4% below MSRP.</p>\r\n<p>Nvidia\'s lower-end graphics cards, however, are still suffering from inflation, with cards like the RTX 3060 and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/nvidia-geforce-rtx-3060-ti-founders-edition-review\">RTX 3060 Ti</a>&nbsp;sitting at above 10% of their MSRPs.</p>\r\n<p>While some graphics cards are still dealing with the impact of the shortage, these new prices are still a notable improvement &mdash; around a year ago, Nvidia\'s graphics cards, which were&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/nvidia-sec-fine-settlement-gaming-gpus-crypto-miners-purchased\">in high demand for cryptocurrency miners,</a>&nbsp;reached around 300% of their original MSRP, while AMD cards peaked at above 200%.</p>\r\n<section data-transform=\"object-feedback\"></section>\r\n<p>As Digital Trends pointed out, new price improvements are likely due to the current cryptocurrency crash as well as supply chain improvements, making graphic cards more readily available and less desirable for crypto farmers.</p>\r\n<p>In February 2021,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/biden-administration-to-review-supply-chains-causing-ps5-xbox-graphics-card-shortages\">Biden signed an executive order</a>&nbsp;pledging to review the supply chain issues causing shortages. Previously, Intel\'s CEO announced that&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/chip-shortage-drag-into-2023-ps5-xbox-series-x-gpu-supply-issues\">the ongoing chip shortage might lead into 2023</a>, though with the new improvements in GPU pricing, it looks like that might not be the case for much longer.</p>', '25. 6. 2022 | 20:00', 1, 8),
(14, 'Virgin Orbit successfully launches satellites during first night mission', 76, 'Virgin Orbit launched a rocket carrying seven satellites from California’s Mojave Air and Space Port early Saturday morning at 1:49 AM ET (10:49PM local), marking the small satellite launcher’s first successful night mission. The company brought the satellites into low Earth orbit with the help of its Boeing 747 carrier aircraft called Cosmic Girl, which had the LauncherOne rocket attached beneath one of its wings.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"WhU3F7\">The mission,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://virginorbit.com/straight-up/\">called Straight Up</a>&nbsp;after a 1988 Paula Abdul song, involved seven research satellites as part of NASA&rsquo;s Space Test Program. Like its previous missions, Virgin Orbit propelled the satellites into space by having Cosmic Girl carry the LauncherOne rocket 35,000 feet above the ground, giving it a headstart before the rocket detaches and launches its payload into orbit. Virgin Orbit&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/30/23189605/virgin-orbit-straight-up-space-force-launcherone\">initially postponed the mission</a> on Thursday after finding that its rocket propellant temperature was &ldquo;slightly out of bounds.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p id=\"HoGSjt\">Virgin Orbit has made five launch attempts in total, but only failed once during&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/5/25/21265057/virgin-orbit-launcherone-rocket-test-launch-747-airplane-cosmic-girl\">its first test flight in May 2020</a>. It has been on a roll&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/1/17/22221212/virgin-orbit-rocket-test-launch-satellites-nasa-branson\">since first reaching orbit in January 2021</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/6/30/22557103/watch-virgin-orbit-launch-debut-commercial-mission-richard-branson\">deploying a set of satellites into orbit in June 2021</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/1/13/22880143/virgin-orbit-launcherone-747-cosmic-girl-air-launch-small-satellites\">completing yet another mission earlier this year</a>. Virgin Orbit&rsquo;s Straight Up mission is the company&rsquo;s fourth successful flight to date.</p>\r\n<p id=\"0wEXbE\">Virgin Orbit is owned by the British billionaire Richard Branson, and isn&rsquo;t to be confused with Virgin Galactic, the company&rsquo;s separate branch for commercial spaceflight. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/8/23/22637711/richard-branson-virgin-orbit-public-spac-satellite-launch\">company went public via a SPAC</a>&nbsp;(special purpose acquisition company) merger last year. While it has completed all its launches from Southern California so far,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://virginorbit.com/the-latest/the-national-reconnaissance-office-is-partnering-with-the-uks-ministry-of-defence-on-historic-mission-aboard-virgin-orbits-launcherone/\">Virgin Orbit plans on taking off from Cornwall, England later this year</a>.</p>', '02. 7. 2022 | 20:28', 1, 3),
(15, 'Meta’s shutting down its digital wallet, Novi', 77, 'Meta’s ending the pilot for Novi, the company’s digital wallet and the last remaining piece of its troubled cryptocurrency project, as first reported by Bloomberg. On Novi’s website, Meta says the wallet is shutting down on September 1st, 2022, and asks users to withdraw their funds “as soon as possible.”', 1, 2, '<p id=\"lmIO3J\">Users will lose access to their accounts come September, and will no longer be able to add money to Novi starting July 21st. If someone forgets to withdraw their remaining balance, Meta says it will &ldquo;attempt to transfer&rdquo; their funds to the bank account or debit card added to the service.</p>\r\n<p id=\"X7WDAo\">Meta&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/10/19/22734487/facebook-novi-digital-wallet-pilot-program-payments-diem-cryptocurrency\">rolled out the &ldquo;small pilot&rdquo; of Novi to users in the US and Guatemala</a>&nbsp;last October. Novi was originally built to support fast and free transactions using the Meta-backed cryptocurrency, Diem, but regulatory challenges forced the company to partner with Coinbase to use the Paxos stablecoin (USDP) instead. While Meta made it clear that it&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/davidmarcus/status/1450447443250728962\">still planned on adding support for Diem</a>&nbsp;at a later date, things started to fall apart (more than they already were) at the end of 2021 and into 2022.</p>\r\n<div class=\"c-float-right\">\r\n<aside id=\"29x4r6\"><q>META WILL UTILIZE THE TECHNOLOGY IT DEVELOPED AS PART OF THE PROJECT &ldquo;ON NEW PRODUCTS, SUCH AS DIGITAL COLLECTIBLES&rdquo;</q></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"fRemVW\">Before&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/10/28/22745234/facebook-new-name-meta-metaverse-zuckerberg-rebrand\">Facebook&rsquo;s parent company was known as Meta</a>, Diem was also known&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/18/18682290/facebook-libra-cryptocurrency-visa-mastercard-digital-currency-calibra-wallet-announce\">by another name: Libra</a>. The cryptocurrency project&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/10/23/20929313/mark-zuckerberg-hearing-congress-libra-calibra-facebook-maxine-waters\">faced scrutiny over its ties to Facebook</a>, so much so that the independent group behind Libra&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2020/12/1/21755078/libra-diem-name-change-cryptocurrency-facebook\">rebranded the project to Diem</a>&nbsp;in an attempt to distance itself from the social network.</p>\r\n<p id=\"RUn03s\">Members of the US Senate&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/10/19/22735171/facebook-novi-diem-libra-calibra-cryptocurrency-digital-wallet-zuckerberg-senate\">called on Meta to shut down its Novi project</a>&nbsp;shortly after its October 2021 launch, citing that the company &ldquo;cannot be trusted to manage cryptocurrency.&rdquo; David Marcus, the head of Meta&rsquo;s cryptocurrency projects,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/11/30/22810220/facebook-crypto-david-marcus-novi-diem-meta\">left the company one month later</a>. Diem&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/1/31/22911426/meta-diem-cryptocurrency-confirms-sale\">sold its assets for about $200 million at the beginning of this year, marking an end to the project</a>.</p>\r\n<p id=\"cdDzuC\">The end of Diem doesn&rsquo;t mean that Meta is ditching the idea of developing its own digital assets and accompanying wallet, though. Meta spokesperson Lauren Dickson said in an emailed statement to&nbsp;<em>The Verge&nbsp;</em>that Meta will utilize the technology it developed in conjunction with the project &ldquo;on new products, such as digital collectibles,&rdquo; as it looks towards &ldquo;building the metaverse.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p id=\"9lneDu\">Meta has already&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/9/23063514/nfts-coming-to-instagram-meta-digital-artwork\">started testing NFTs (non-fungible tokens) on Instagram</a>&nbsp;and recently rolled out support for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2022/06/30/facebook-testing-nfts-select-creators-us/\">NFTs on Facebook for select creators based in the US</a>. The company is also reportedly&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/4/6/23013896/meta-facebook-zuck-bucks-finance-financial-services-products\">working on a digital currency, called &ldquo;Zuck Bucks,&rdquo;</a>&nbsp;that&rsquo;s not based on the blockchain.</p>\r\n<p id=\"EMhjXN\">Last month,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/22/23179058/mark-zuckerberg-meta-pay-wallet-metaverse-details\">Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg also hinted at creating a digital wallet</a>&nbsp;that could help you manage and store &ldquo;digital clothing, art, videos, music, experiences, virtual events, and more.&rdquo; The wallet would be interoperable across different metaverse experiences, reflecting the goals of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/21/23176755/microsoft-meta-epic-metaverse-standards-forum-founded\">Metaverse Standards Forum that Meta and a group of other companies helped form</a>, which calls for industry-wide standards across virtual reality and augmented reality experiences.</p>\r\n<div class=\"m-ad m-ad__dynamic_ad_unit m-ad__desktop_article_body dfp_ad-wrapper--is-filled\" data-concert-ads-name=\"desktop_article_body\">\r\n<div id=\"div-gpt-ad-desktop_article_body\" class=\"dynamic-js-slot dfp_ad--held-area dfp_ad--rendered dfp_ad--is-filled\" data-google-query-id=\"CPCwreXq2vgCFc3PEQgd4PkNRQ\"></div>\r\n</div>', '02. 7. 2022 | 20:29', 1, 2),
(17, 'How to delete your Instagram account', 78, 'If you’ve made the decision to delete Instagram, whether because you’ve outgrown the need for a certain finsta or because its parent company Meta is courting controversy again, doing so isn’t as quick or easy as it should be. Up until recently, it couldn’t even be done from within the Instagram app.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"GXkBWc\">Go ahead and take a moment to make an obligatory &ldquo;I&rsquo;m deleting Instagram&rdquo; post if you&rsquo;d like. After that, you have two ways you can go about it.</p>\r\n<h2 id=\"ZnlHHx\">DELETING INSTAGRAM USING THE IOS OR ANDROID APP</h2>\r\n<p id=\"5kaerh\">The easiest way for iPhone users to delete Instagram is by using the app. To do so, go to your&nbsp;<strong>profile</strong>, tap the&nbsp;<strong>hamburger menu</strong>&nbsp;in the top right, and select&nbsp;<strong>Settings</strong>. Then go to&nbsp;<strong>Account</strong>, and scroll down to the bottom of the menu. There will be a&nbsp;<strong>Delete Account</strong>&nbsp;button under the&nbsp;<strong>Branded Content</strong>&nbsp;button.</p>\r\n<p id=\"nKzpIg\">If you have it, tapping on it will bring up a menu asking if you want to delete or deactivate your account &mdash; you can read more about those other options in the &ldquo;Temporarily suspending your Instagram account&rdquo; section of this how-to. Pressing the&nbsp;<strong>Delete account</strong>&nbsp;button will bring up a message saying that you can stop the deletion process by a certain date if you log back in.</p>\r\n<p id=\"B1WOuu\">Tap the red&nbsp;<strong>Continue deleting account</strong>&nbsp;button, and the app will open a webpage. Here, you can complete the deletion process after you answer a question about why you&rsquo;re deleting your account, and enter your password to confirm.</p>\r\n<p id=\"SI1zCa\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/24/23140416/apple-app-store-policy-account-delete-events-in-app-payments\">Apple&rsquo;s rules</a>&nbsp;mean that Instagram&rsquo;s iOS app has to let you delete your account. In our testing, the option hasn&rsquo;t always been available on the Android version of the app. You can check for the&nbsp;<strong>Delete Account</strong>&nbsp;option by following the instructions for iOS above, but if you don&rsquo;t have it, you&rsquo;ll have to do it using the web.</p>\r\n<h2 id=\"3Ytff4\">DELETING INSTAGRAM ON THE WEB</h2>\r\n<p id=\"fupkMg\">If you can&rsquo;t use the app to delete your account, you&rsquo;ll have to follow these steps to ditch your account &mdash; they can be followed using either a computer or phone, as long as you&rsquo;re using a browser.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li id=\"gvs2T0\">First, you&rsquo;ll have to go to Instagram&rsquo;s special account removal request page,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://instagram.com/accounts/remove/request/permanent/\">which can be found here</a>, or by following the link in Instagram&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://help.instagram.com/370452623149242/\">account deletion help article</a>. If you&rsquo;re not logged into Instagram for the web (most people won&rsquo;t be), you&rsquo;ll have to enter your credentials. In fact, it&rsquo;s very likely you&rsquo;ll have to put in your password twice throughout the deletion process, so now&rsquo;s probably a good time to make sure you know what it is.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656783206_1796_283024\" data-cdata=\"{\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/P_ppbq53euaCd1xIdq2sHTSceDo=/0x0:2148x1032/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4Gzyx--aQvcW8aWFO_Jeln3cX7Y=/0x0:2148x1032/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jOK5Akyax2KBYMd4XdTymSK0gnw=/0x0:2148x1032/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nqxh2mlvRuTGfQjwTkPZiveUZYg=/0x0:2148x1032/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jCUi-dmTUJr8zMNS9Bq4ii6E-C0=/0x0:2148x1032/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tQjXdX2DhWbsZjDtntf_hCVIMWA=/0x0:2148x1032/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TiVvvN0vJ-fPrLOI5DVqFT70jVg=/0x0:2148x1032/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jqnyIniFxuzsmDAtkUohMo0WsKs=/0x0:2148x1032/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MMU2qPCg1pdRglYq3SJaIoidLfs=/0x0:2148x1032/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7Tv-5JDaYNoteWML0wW_QkQULjI=/0x0:2148x1032/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vvtQI2M4NiiiSoipoDTEDIsj1V8=/0x0:2148x1032/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/aTgVr5VmjrP0m96JEWtZTefaamM=/0x0:2148x1032/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/iRE1DuEPJLZTEwe81L1ckAiJdJ4=/0x0:2148x1032/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1I8ilW08CSFQ-6AFmGGhti_4Q-M=/0x0:2148x1032/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/isBQrhFytEaFfY2vMJrxzlUjeMk=/0x0:2148x1032/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/t6FatowbFSpejVRbZ1XjEPavJtM=/0x0:2148x1032/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PdeId2aX-SkIMYp-wpiGKk8X5Yw=/0x0:2148x1032/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/W7M2-HYa3iy5RHG0Qmuq2teRun8=/0x0:2148x1032/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nDtF5NQpcnpS_OVzBjXUh0K2b-U=/0x0:2148x1032/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2148x1032):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021933/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.28.png 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"2148\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>Instagram will clearly show you what account you&rsquo;re about to delete, and ask you why.</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li id=\"zM0tgA\">You should end up on a page with the old Instagram logo and a dropdown asking you why you want to delete your account. Depending on which option you choose, you may be shown various links to Instagram&rsquo;s help center promising to fix your issues or a message helpfully reminding you to check which account you&rsquo;re deleting.</li>\r\n<li id=\"NmkzRk\">Whichever you pick, there&rsquo;ll be a box below the links that asks you to reenter your password. After you do, tap or click the button that says&nbsp;<strong>Delete (your account name)</strong>, and confirm that you&rsquo;re sure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656783206_1524_283025\" data-cdata=\"{\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ublY82P5pItuMxbhGc3NrR_qthc=/0x0:2146x1350/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UVSZ79pNwX0l1dbETCCVOieuub4=/0x0:2146x1350/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/L_U-DxGrTtrk2pQRo948ngJWsRw=/0x0:2146x1350/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CRloZEVOquv5FQmup40TVNb1Tck=/0x0:2146x1350/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/i14FgNkDHmLCRwc9xPzUBbRANGM=/0x0:2146x1350/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Fh-jvD5GutR-3CNUVQP2Z5hP79Q=/0x0:2146x1350/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tW7i5ahLObMMIkTcsdNORLRpTLg=/0x0:2146x1350/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kurEfX_JqmE1TekFGQhoJQeCWvQ=/0x0:2146x1350/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3SOrjplKidbImhf701QpWyh53cA=/0x0:2146x1350/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/rtkobUbeMvxM5VsGfaqjfO2bnX4=/0x0:2146x1350/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sjumxO8oeyb8HydtmQ3OjWUruRc=/0x0:2146x1350/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/W7kDPwRcLva-PLChdW0snwLF5Ds=/0x0:2146x1350/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/njHtMQsPjXiSu6OpgJU0UAjC4N8=/0x0:2146x1350/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ERdmS8vwXCkjExnpKZgX-VALCIU=/0x0:2146x1350/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OJA9Qxd_9wBSlm0FNwhI-MDlk-I=/0x0:2146x1350/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TIHTBkMcxi2MCDkjXF2s5cb_-kA=/0x0:2146x1350/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vuBg5YW22_pJLV5nqXyq0r77rag=/0x0:2146x1350/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/k82bylAYMM4Qwh32kpB2_NlxYq8=/0x0:2146x1350/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/scU-QvbmtfEjwY031RLE3asmJfo=/0x0:2146x1350/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2146x1350):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021908/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.29.59.png 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"2146\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>Tapping the delete button after entering your password will give you one last confirmation pop-up.</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"6Mvlqk\">As Instagram says a few times on the account deletion page, your data won&rsquo;t be immediately erased &mdash; Meta will keep it around for 30 days. But your profile and posts will be hidden on the site.</p>\r\n<p id=\"8KTPKH\">If you&rsquo;re completely breaking up with Instagram, don&rsquo;t forget to remove the app from your phone as well. Doing so will save you a little space and will also put a little bit of friction between you and signing back up for the service.</p>\r\n<h2 id=\"M73fM8\">HOW TO UN-DELETE YOUR INSTAGRAM ACCOUNT</h2>\r\n<p id=\"jSovZG\">Be aware that you won&rsquo;t be able to bring your account back if it&rsquo;s been over 30 days since you asked Instagram to delete it. You&rsquo;ll have to recreate your account (your username will be freed up after your account&rsquo;s deleted, but it&rsquo;s possible someone could&rsquo;ve taken it).</p>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656783206_8791_283026\" data-cdata=\"{\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ugPZy0MQ-2dv68HhSKE0FD4N4oI=/0x0:1420x1196/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/hcbjpaZvpxHDvai4RdiyE7CW3es=/0x0:1420x1196/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fCwZlF48FMjiTaYacn0ePuNCthg=/0x0:1420x1196/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6LDaNcszmEcxc0isYkL9LMEAMUo=/0x0:1420x1196/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/24usBnayJWi4swF-7lSLNnbaMFc=/0x0:1420x1196/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6w9psZfvcD015XVMR10vuew-WWE=/0x0:1420x1196/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/JEaGAmIL0FrNZ3irBcT0fWkDnOQ=/0x0:1420x1196/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/E4SfpGwgwi4OAGYNtDO5guMEqfE=/0x0:1420x1196/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wZdTD91I0H1cNu-ZLEWw07k_39E=/0x0:1420x1196/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kQztrU_2Hiwyn4L6ydPFl3dLlko=/0x0:1420x1196/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/p2vyc3MBhre9iCo4I7YJ0vegX7o=/0x0:1420x1196/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Lg_5ZqhScJdH_mQzEsQ8dSCtVew=/0x0:1420x1196/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8IcKXI8bjVhQDXEy_X7GqusXAVw=/0x0:1420x1196/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vTAw5KKYevBR7ffohAzdUyD1T38=/0x0:1420x1196/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/aVEhk_qnfJNfrJr-Xt4tMIqBOWY=/0x0:1420x1196/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LaCnMH7yeBXCifwWoF8TZmYsYLY=/0x0:1420x1196/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Gd6rL9HJmVy0h-uA5iHPCjXp6Js=/0x0:1420x1196/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OjTSS2GGAarx0_-c__BvJRoDuCA=/0x0:1420x1196/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-QnrZ6AhQ46Ah2Sldot10mm9inM=/0x0:1420x1196/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:1420x1196):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021936/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.34.26.png 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"1420\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>You can restore your account within 30 days by logging back in.</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"X7znk6\">However, if you&rsquo;re within that 30-day time period, you can get your account back, along with its posts and DMs. To do so, simply go back to Instagram and log in with your credentials. You&rsquo;ll see a message saying that you requested your account be deleted, along with the date your data will be gone. To keep that from happening, just press the &ldquo;Keep Account&rdquo; button.</p>\r\n<h2 id=\"dsYjWz\">TEMPORARILY SUSPENDING YOUR INSTAGRAM ACCOUNT</h2>\r\n<p id=\"5K7FJt\">If you want to remove your account from public view, but don&rsquo;t want to permanently delete all your photos and messages, you can suspend your account instead.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021984/IG_Suspend_Account.gif\"><img class=\"c-dynamic-image  lazy-image lazy-loaded\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wwQuQv-C3WZ9ugO0FYNNTx4rnZg=/800x0/filters:no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021984/IG_Suspend_Account.gif\" alt=\"\" data-chorus-optimize-field=\"main_image\" data-cid=\"site/dynamic_size_image-1656783206_1620_283027\" data-cdata=\"{\"></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>The screen to suspend your account is relatively easy to access, but you&rsquo;ll have to do it through a web browser.</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"EVZr6c\">Again, Meta makes you use the web version of Instagram, instead of the app, but at least you won&rsquo;t have to get a link from a help article.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li id=\"wXlcLh\">After logging into Instagram.com, go to your profile and click the Edit Profile button (if you&rsquo;re using a mobile browser, you&rsquo;ll have to tap the settings cog to get the option).</li>\r\n<li id=\"EaspiW\">From there, go to&nbsp;<strong>Edit Profile&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Temporarily disable my account</strong>&nbsp;(it&rsquo;ll be an option at the very bottom). As with deleting your account, you&rsquo;ll have to select a reason why you&rsquo;re suspending your account, and put in your password.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<figure class=\"e-image\"><span class=\"e-image__inner\"><span class=\"e-image__image \" data-original=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png\"><picture class=\"c-picture\" data-cid=\"site/picture_element-1656783206_4914_283028\" data-cdata=\"{\"><source srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VdgTjHnsiZXZ5secex85jGzlEkg=/0x0:2126x1568/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/a4zCs2jaSfzCWJkiknj0t8mDw-w=/0x0:2126x1568/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/x_-BXHTFv3nQSVnkw0tfP781MrQ=/0x0:2126x1568/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VxLmc45JGuhg90D4jTeJeaONCfs=/0x0:2126x1568/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tqC3Zllv3yJJQrDZkRSyao3Tto4=/0x0:2126x1568/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Up07ZbQWgAMNgeq3KVCPGzvDBdM=/0x0:2126x1568/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/mP7Q9hjCtuFl7Od7U5JigWXOba4=/0x0:2126x1568/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/4y3jNVzzQxUw2SKZuz0UTxuMV14=/0x0:2126x1568/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/icnNtDXr5L0rQQB3OdWpQS7cccs=/0x0:2126x1568/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1920w\" type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\"><img src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Era44AcXS0b-HE7n0Davdryw-mU=/0x0:2126x1568/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1221px) 846px, (min-width: 880px) calc(100vw - 334px), 100vw\" srcset=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nx3VdVvNGeaJOSZZjMUP2rJzrSw=/0x0:2126x1568/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-6Nh3dWq8FnnEsdAQ8JXi8RRTao=/0x0:2126x1568/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-KVlO7x5pDt6YworllmAxXBxpIU=/0x0:2126x1568/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/CtlcH6WNHBN6MBL4hLqjsODXQ48=/0x0:2126x1568/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RRZefMSJHlUmtWjNzx14Ly2Mor0=/0x0:2126x1568/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KnpLW3AYkoPlmm8T-Q71cd4epuQ=/0x0:2126x1568/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HOEKXlwxccfG3YplYMGR-Ejp2zc=/0x0:2126x1568/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gtya0rYZirfhZvoV2yhrH9pQetg=/0x0:2126x1568/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_aqb3tHD8OmxsfC0st7Dol_piZI=/0x0:2126x1568/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2126x1568):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/23021966/Screen_Shot_2021_11_17_at_08.40.08.png 1920w\" alt=\"\" data-upload-width=\"2126\"></picture></span></span>\r\n<figcaption><em>Instagram&rsquo;s &ldquo;Temporarily disable account&rdquo; screen.</em></figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n<p id=\"mKFdXV\">To re-enable your account, simply log back in using the app or the website. You&rsquo;ll only be able to suspend your account once a week, so if you accidentally log back in your profile, your posts will be back online and visible to followers, at least for a little while.</p>', '02. 7. 2022 | 20:31', 1, 1),
(25, 'Crypto hedge fund Three Arrows files for bankruptcy', 82, 'Cryptocurrency hedge fund Three Arrows Capital (3AC) filed for Chapter 15 bankruptcy in a bid to protect its US assets from creditors in the country, as reported earlier by Bloomberg and CNBC. Representatives for the Singapore-based company made the filing in a Southern District New York court on Friday, which legally protects the US assets of insolvent foreign debtors from creditors in the US.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"UjYYyj\">Founded in 2012 by Kyle Davis and Su Zhu, 3AC&nbsp;<a href=\"https://fortune.com/2022/06/16/crypto-crash-hedge-fund-three-arrows-capital-insolvency-rumors-novogratz/\">managed about $10 billion in assets as recently as March</a>, later sinking&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/battered-crypto-hedge-fund-three-arrows-capital-considers-asset-sales-bailout-11655469932\">to $3 billion in April</a>. Like several other crypto firms,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/17/23172539/3ac-celsius-babel-crypto-loans-hedge-funds-uh-oh\">including the lending giants Celcius and Babel Finance</a>, 3AC&rsquo;s turn in fortunes is part of the so-called crypto &ldquo;winter&rdquo; that&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/5/12/23069232/terra-luna-collapse-stablecoins-crypto-crash-bitcoin\">brought down stablecoins</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/6/13/23165611/bitcoin-ethereum-crypto-price-drop-celsius\">sent Bitcoin&rsquo;s value plunging</a>.</p>\r\n<div id=\"rPCiRO\"><iframe title=\"Three Arrows Capital bankruptcy filing (Hosted by DocumentCloud)\" src=\"https://embed.documentcloud.org/documents/22077923-three-arrows-capital-bankruptcy-filing/?embed=1&amp;responsive=0&amp;title=1&amp;onlyshoworg=1\" width=\"700\" height=\"600\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-forms allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></div>\r\n<p id=\"PYF3Ra\">Earlier this week, reports emerged that&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2022/06/29/crypto-hedge-fund-three-arrows-capital-plunges-into-liquidation.html\">3AC failed to pay a $670 million loan</a>&nbsp;provided by crypto broker Voyager Digital, which&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2022/07/01/voyager-digital-suspends-all-trading-deposits-and-withdrawals-.html\">has since halted all trades, deposits, and withdrawals</a>&nbsp;as a result.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://news.sky.com/story/crypto-hedge-fund-three-arrows-capital-plunges-into-liquidation-12642402\"><em>Sky News</em>&nbsp;later reported</a>&nbsp;that a court in the British Virgin Islands has ordered 3AC&rsquo;s liquidation and that the firm is reportedly working with business consulting company Teneo to oversee the process.</p>\r\n<p id=\"Pg3JHP\">In May, Davies and Zhu admitted in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/battered-crypto-hedge-fund-three-arrows-capital-considers-asset-sales-bailout-11655469932\">an interview with the&nbsp;<em>WSJ</em></a>&nbsp;that the company lost out on a $200 million investment following&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/terrausd-crash-led-to-vanished-savings-shattered-dreams-11653649201\">the crash of Luna and its sister coin TerraUSD</a>. At the time, the two remained optimistic about the prospects of crypto, telling the&nbsp;<em>WSJ</em>&nbsp;that they&rsquo;ve &ldquo;always been crypto believers&rdquo; and &ldquo;still are.&rdquo;</p>', '03. 7. 2022 | 15:09', 1, 0),
(26, 'Tesla’s run of record quarterly deliveries comes to an end thanks to China’s COVID shutdowns', 83, 'Tesla announced it had delivered 254,695 vehicles during the second quarter of 2022, about an 18 percent drop from the previous quarter. The report, which was published on Tesla’s site, signals an end to a nearly two-year-long run of record quarterly deliveries for Elon Musk’s company, which can mostly be attributed to lengthy COVID-related shutdowns of its factory in Shanghai.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"QjM3X5\">Tesla said the Model 3 and Model Y vehicles made up 238,533 of these deliveries, while 16,162 were for the Model S and Model X vehicles. On the production side of things, Tesla said it managed to build a total of 258,580 vehicles.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div id=\"uRKSpk\"><iframe id=\"datawrapper-chart-jDTlr\" title=\"Tesla deliveries by quarter\" src=\"https://datawrapper.dwcdn.net/jDTlr/1/\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" aria-label=\"Stacked Column Chart\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"pa6BTX\"></p>\r\n<p id=\"wVvsSU\">China has been crucial to the company&rsquo;s rise to its status as one of the most valuable automakers in the world. But Tesla&rsquo;s Shanghai Gigafactory has been caught in a seemingly endless loop of openings and closures in recent months, as the nation&rsquo;s strict COVID lockdown policy has taken its toll.</p>\r\n<p id=\"GrRcHP\">In March,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/business/autos-transportation/exclusive-tesla-stops-work-shanghai-factory-two-days-amid-china-covid-curbs-2022-03-16/\">Tesla shuttered its Shanghai factory for two days</a>&nbsp;amid a spike in COVID-19 cases, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-03-31/tesla-extends-shanghai-plant-shutdown-again-as-outbreak-persists\">closed the factory once again</a>&nbsp;in April as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-04-02/entire-shanghai-placed-under-lockdown-as-covid-cases-surge\">Shanghai continues to grapple with a city-wide lockdown</a>. The Shanghai plant is the company&rsquo;s largest, producing both Model 3s and Model Ys.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div id=\"ID6UPi\"><iframe id=\"datawrapper-chart-VVgVh\" title=\"Tesla production by quarter\" src=\"https://datawrapper.dwcdn.net/VVgVh/2/\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" aria-label=\"Stacked Column Chart\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"NTd50D\"></p>\r\n<p id=\"hfyOcl\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/3/22/22808108/tesla-gigafactory-open-production-start-elon-musk\">Tesla recently opened its first European factory</a>&nbsp;in Berlin, Germany, and held a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23023458/tesla-elon-musk-cyber-rodeo-austin-texas-gigafactory\">&ldquo;cyber rodeo&rdquo; to celebrate the grand opening of its Austin, Texas Gigafactory</a>&nbsp;&mdash; both of which could help offset production issues caused by the COVID-related lockdowns in Shanghai. Musk recently described both factories as &ldquo;gigantic money furnaces&rdquo; that are &ldquo;losing billions of dollars&rdquo; as supply chain constraints continue to constrain the company&rsquo;s plans.</p>', '03. 7. 2022 | 15:09', 1, 4),
(27, 'Steve Jobs awarded posthumous Medal of Freedom by President Biden', 84, 'Steve Jobs, the co-founder and former CEO of Apple, has been awarded a posthumous Presidential Medal of Freedom by President Joe Biden, the White House announced Friday. The Presidential Medal of Freedom is the highest US honor that can be given to a civilian, and it’s presented to “individuals who have made exemplary contributions to the prosperity, values, or security of the United States, world peace, or other significant societal, public or private endeavors,” the White House said in a statement.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"EExtdg\">Jobs founded Apple in April 1976, and it&rsquo;s since become one of the biggest companies in the world. He helped launch many tech products that have gone on to become cultural touchstones, including the Mac, the iPod, and the iPhone. He died&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2011/10/6/2473035/apple-steve-jobs-has-died\">on October 5th, 2011</a>.</p>\r\n<p id=\"HGpbA8\">Broadly popular in his lifetime, Jobs described himself as &ldquo;disappointed&rdquo; with President Obama in Walter Isaacson&rsquo;s biography. &ldquo;He&rsquo;s having trouble leading because he&rsquo;s reluctant to offend people or piss them off,&rdquo; Jobs&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.cbsnews.com/news/steve-jobs-obamas-focus-on-excuses-infuriated-him/\">is quoted as saying</a>. &ldquo;That&rsquo;s not a problem I ever had.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p id=\"3zEqZs\">In its statement, the White House praised Jobs&rsquo;s creative approach to his various endeavors. &ldquo;Steve Jobs was the co-founder, chief executive, and chair of Apple, Inc., CEO of Pixar and held a leading role at the Walt Disney Company,&rdquo; the White House wrote. &ldquo;His vision, imagination and creativity led to inventions that have, and continue to, change the way the world communicates, as well as transforming the computer, music, film and wireless industries.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p id=\"h2ZpYG\">The award will be presented on July 7th. This year&rsquo;s Presidential Medal of Freedom recipients also include Simone Biles, Gabrielle Giffords, John McCain, Megan Rapinoe, and Denzel Washington. You can see&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/statements-releases/2022/07/01/president-biden-announces-recipients-of-the-presidential-medal-of-freedom/\">the full list here</a>.</p>', '04. 7. 2022 | 16:52', 1, 8);
INSERT INTO `article` (`id`, `title`, `title_image_id`, `perex`, `author_id`, `category_id`, `content`, `date_added`, `is_published`, `views`) VALUES
(28, 'PayPal is ending fee-free Friends & Family payments for business accounts', 85, 'PayPal is putting new limits on a feature in its payment system that allows people to receive money without paying extra fees, the company recently announced. Starting July 28th, only personal PayPal accounts will be able to get funds via Friends & Family, a transaction method intended for trusted recipients.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"5MVhgJ\">There are two ways of sending money on PayPal: Friends &amp; Family and Goods &amp; Services. F&amp;F is intended for paying your friend back for dinner, for example, or giving your kid some birthday money &mdash; you know who&rsquo;s receiving the funds and what you&rsquo;re paying them for. There&rsquo;s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/us/webapps/mpp/paypal-fees#SendAndReceiveMoney\">typically no fee</a>&nbsp;involved, but it also drops protections for issues that might come up, like refunds or scams.</p>\r\n<p id=\"hhTzzj\">G&amp;S is intended for purchases, and money sent this way is subject to PayPal fees. Everyone hates fees! But with G&amp;S, if the thing you buy isn&rsquo;t as described, it&rsquo;s damaged when it arrives, or it just never gets to the buyer, you can often easily get a refund for the purchase.</p>\r\n<p id=\"QjOqVg\">Many businesses handle transactions using a PayPal business account and take payments for goods and services through F&amp;F, even though you&rsquo;re technically not supposed to. The buyer might not realize the difference or care, or the business and the customer could agree to send cash that way to avoid seller fees. This is fairly common in many informal transactions, like people selling things on social media platforms &mdash; perhaps the buyer knows the seller personally and trusts that they&rsquo;ll deliver. Sometimes sellers insist on F&amp;F to avoid transaction fees, which causes problems if something goes wrong down the line.</p>\r\n<p id=\"9whnt9\">The change is already&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/KiraBuckland/status/1542720730587996161\">causing frustration</a>&nbsp;on the part of some creators, who use PayPal to run their business and will now be subject to additional transaction fees.</p>\r\n<p id=\"Auuk3P\">With this new change, US business accounts won&rsquo;t be able to accept fee-free personal payments, and people who use PayPal for their company will need to create a personal account to receive money fee-free from friends and family.</p>\r\n<p id=\"FETgKB\">PayPal didn&rsquo;t immediately respond to questions about whether it changed the rules to crack down on miscategorized purchases but said in the announcement the tweak will &ldquo;drive consistency on [the] platform&rdquo; and &ldquo;[remove] confusion around which payments are eligible for buyer and seller protections.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p id=\"uvfqrW\">In the same announcement, PayPal also said the transaction fee structure for goods and services would change beginning later this month. Currently, sellers pay 2.89 percent plus $0.49 per transaction, but starting July 28th, that will change to 2.99 percent without an additional flat fee.</p>', '04. 7. 2022 | 16:54', 1, 2),
(29, 'Twitch is testing channel surfing', 86, 'Twitch is testing a new way to discover new channels that reminds me of the good old days of channel surfing on my TV. The experiment, which it calls the Channel Switcher, lets you easily flip through previews of a bunch of different streams to help you find something to watch. And perhaps best of all, you won’t see ads while using it.', 1, 2, '<p id=\"BXYV4d\">You can get an idea of how it works&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/Twitch/status/1542596191715618816\">in this tweet from Twitch</a>:</p>\r\n<div id=\"hCqYCu\">\r\n<div class=\"twitter-tweet twitter-tweet-rendered\"><iframe id=\"twitter-widget-0\" class=\"\" title=\"Twitter Tweet\" src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/embed/Tweet.html?dnt=false&amp;embedId=twitter-widget-0&amp;%3D%3D&amp;frame=false&amp;hideCard=false&amp;hideThread=true&amp;id=1542596191715618816&amp;lang=en&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2022%2F7%2F1%2F23191626%2Ftwitch-channel-switcher-test-experiment&amp;sessionId=63b569d2add7b3a45e3327530f56a1fe40612cff&amp;siteScreenName=verge&amp;theme=light&amp;widgetsVersion=b45a03c79d4c1%3A1654150928467&amp;width=550px\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-tweet-id=\"1542596191715618816\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"ne9iO0\">Right now on Twitch, if you don&rsquo;t already know what you want to watch, it can be difficult to find something new that you might actually want to tune into. Personally, my rundown is to check the homepage, scan the sidebar of people I follow, click into an individual game or category to browse who is live, or navigate directly to a streamer&rsquo;s account.</p>\r\n<p id=\"DCgsZi\">But, if I want to move on from a stream I&rsquo;m already watching, my best options are to click another followed account or recommendation on the sidebar or back out to Twitch&rsquo;s Browse section. That latter option isn&rsquo;t my favorite, as I often run into choice paralysis.</p>\r\n<div class=\"c-float-right\">\r\n<aside id=\"UW6tRX\"><q>YOU&rsquo;LL BE ABLE TO WATCH A 60-SECOND PREVIEW</q></aside>\r\n</div>\r\n<p id=\"3kufCg\">Channel Switcher looks like it will be a much quicker way to check out many different streamers. You&rsquo;ll be able to watch a 60-second preview of a stream before having to decide to click through or watch another channel, according to Twitch spokesperson Ashton Williams.</p>\r\n<p id=\"tK0Qg9\">It seems like only a lucky few will be able to try Channel Switcher for the moment, though. Williams says that &ldquo;only a small percentage of users who are logged in&rdquo; currently have access, and those who get it have been randomly selected. The experiment will be turned off in the middle of July so the company can analyze the results of the test, but Williams notes that Twitch plans to work on future iterations and may offer an opt-in version of the feature.</p>\r\n<p>Channel Switcher is just one of many updates Twitch announced on Thursday, including a new tool that makes it easier for streamers to add guests to their stream called&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/Twitch/status/1542587624589631488\">Guest Star</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://twitter.com/Twitch/status/1542600377425600521\">the ability to create your own tags</a>.</p>', '04. 7. 2022 | 16:55', 1, 4),
(66, 'Prices in Turkey rise at fastest pace for 24 years', 89, 'Prices in Turkey are rising at their fastest rate in 24 years, according to the latest official figures.', 1, 3, '<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The annual rate of inflation, the pace at which prices rise, hit 78.62% in June, which was slightly higher than expectations.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Transport costs and housing saw some of the sharpest price rises, worsened by the Ukraine war.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Inflation has surged since last year, when the Turkish president cut interest rates to try to boost the economy.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Usually countries would increase interest rates in an attempt to cool inflation. But President Recep Tayyip Erdogan has described interest rates as \"the mother and father of all evil\", and has used more unorthodox policy to try to dampen prices including intervening in foreign exchange markets.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Last year\'s cut in interest rates from 19% to 14% has led to a fall in the value of the Turkish lira, which means it costs more for the country to import goods from abroad.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"piano-inline1\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">In the latest inflation figures, transportation saw the biggest rise in costs, climbing 123% over the past year.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Food and non-alcoholic beverages were close behind with price rises of 94%, while the cost of furnishings and household equipment was up 81%.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The overall inflation figure was the highest since September 1998, when annual inflation hit 80.4% and Turkey was battling to end a decade of chronically high inflation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810\" data-component=\"image-block\">\r\n<figure class=\"ssrcss-wpgbih-StyledFigure e34k3c23\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21\"><span class=\"ssrcss-1exovz1-Placeholder e16icw910\"><img class=\"ssrcss-evoj7m-Image ee0ct7c0\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/640/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 800w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 976w\" alt=\"2px presentational grey line\" width=\"640\" height=\"2\" loading=\"lazy\"></span></div>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-dm4ypg-ComponentWrapper-HeadlineComponentWrapper e1xue1i89\" data-component=\"subheadline-block\">\r\n<h2 id=\"Analysis-Erdogans-gamble\" class=\"ssrcss-y2fd7s-StyledHeading e1fj1fc10\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span role=\"text\">Analysis: Erdogan\'s gamble</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\"><strong class=\"ssrcss-hmf8ql-BoldText e5tfeyi3\">By Victoria Craig, BBC business correspondent</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">As inflation in Turkey continues to smoulder, the nation\'s economy is also contending with the effects of a plunging currency value. The Turkish lira has shed nearly half its value in the past year. That means consumer spending power is in decline as the cost of goods and services continue to skyrocket.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Despite reaching a 24-year high in June, economists had expected the inflation rate to rise even further. This is the second month in a row official data has missed forecasts, and that is continuing to stoke concern about the reliability of official data from Turkey\'s statistics agency. Helping to fan those flames: ahead of the release of May\'s inflation data, the head of the price statistics department resigned citing health reasons.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"piano-inline2\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">While times are tough for people living and working in Turkey, favourable exchange rates are helping lure international travellers to the country for summer holidays. But Turkish holidaymakers are coming in fewer numbers than in the past, and to afford it, they\'re staying fewer days and paying off the cost of travel over 10-12 months.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810\" data-component=\"image-block\">\r\n<figure class=\"ssrcss-wpgbih-StyledFigure e34k3c23\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21\"><span class=\"ssrcss-1exovz1-Placeholder e16icw910\"><img class=\"ssrcss-evoj7m-Image ee0ct7c0\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/640/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 800w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 976w\" alt=\"2px presentational grey line\" width=\"640\" height=\"2\" loading=\"lazy\"></span></div>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The surge in prices is making it tough for businesses.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">\"I\'ve never experienced a season like this before,\" said hotelier Volkan Yorulmaz, the general manager of Kemer Holiday Club in Antalya. \"I can\'t budget my spending because the costs change from day to day. The all-inclusive concept is no longer sustainable.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">\"Over 50% of our guests come from Russia or Ukraine, so without them, the beginning of the season was a little problematic.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">\"Turkish people are trying to come on holiday. They use credit cards, or pay in instalments, or are shortening their planned holidays, to make it affordable for them.\"</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '04. 7. 2022 | 21:31', 1, 8),
(67, 'Sri Lanka energy minister warns petrol stocks about to run dry', 90, 'Sri Lanka\'s energy minister has issued a stark warning over the country\'s fuel stocks as it faces its worst economic crisis in more than 70 years.', 1, 3, '<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">On Sunday, Kanchana Wijesekera said the nation only had enough petrol left for less than a day under regular demand.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">He also said its next petrol shipment was not due for more than two weeks.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Last week, Sri Lanka suspended sales of petrol and diesel for non-essential vehicles as it struggles to pay for imports like fuel, food and medicines.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Mr Wijesekera told reporters that the country had 12,774 tonnes of diesel and 4,061 tonnes of petrol left in its reserves.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">\"The next petrol shipment is expected between the 22nd and 23rd [of July],\" he added.</p>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">A shipment of diesel is expected to arrive at the weekend, however Mr Wijesekera warned that the country does not have enough money to pay for planned fuel and crude oil imports.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">He said Sri Lanka\'s central bank could only supply $125m for fuel purchases, far less than the $587m needed for its scheduled shipments.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Mr Wijesekera added that the country owed $800m to seven suppliers for purchases it made earlier this year.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Last week Sri Lanka&nbsp;<a class=\"ssrcss-k17ofw-InlineLink e1no5rhv0\" href=\"https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-61961821\">banned sales of fuel for private vehicles</a>&nbsp;for two week.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Experts believe it is the first country to take the drastic step of halting sales of petrol to ordinary people since the 1970s oil crisis, when fuel was rationed in the US and Europe.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810\" data-component=\"image-block\">\r\n<figure class=\"ssrcss-wpgbih-StyledFigure e34k3c23\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21\"><span class=\"ssrcss-1hq4gmv-Placeholder e16icw910\"><img class=\"ssrcss-evoj7m-Image ee0ct7c0\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/9281/production/_125750573_gettyimages-1241632095.jpg\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/9281/production/_125750573_gettyimages-1241632095.jpg 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/9281/production/_125750573_gettyimages-1241632095.jpg 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/9281/production/_125750573_gettyimages-1241632095.jpg 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/9281/production/_125750573_gettyimages-1241632095.jpg 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/9281/production/_125750573_gettyimages-1241632095.jpg 800w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/9281/production/_125750573_gettyimages-1241632095.jpg 976w\" alt=\"A protest\" width=\"976\" height=\"549\" loading=\"lazy\"></span><span class=\"ssrcss-tvuve5-StyledFigureCopyright e34k3c20\" role=\"text\"><span class=\"visually-hidden ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0\">IMAGE SOURCE,</span>GETTY IMAGES</span></div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"ssrcss-1mget3o-StyledFigureCaption e34k3c22\"><span class=\"visually-hidden ssrcss-1f39n02-VisuallyHidden e1y6uwnp0\">Image caption,</span>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-y7krbn-Stack e1y4nx260\">The country has seen protests</div>\r\n</figcaption>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The island nation of 22 million people is facing its worst economic crisis since gaining independence from the UK in 1948 as it lacks enough foreign currency to pay for imports of essential goods.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"piano-inline2\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Acute shortages of fuel, food and medicines have helped to push up the cost of living to record highs in the country, where many people rely on motor vehicles for their livelihoods. It\'s also sparked violent street protests.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The government blames the Covid pandemic, which affected Sri Lanka\'s tourist trade - one of its biggest foreign currency earners. However, many experts say economic mismanagement is to blame.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">In May the country failed to make a payment on its foreign debt for the first time in its history.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810\" data-component=\"image-block\">\r\n<figure class=\"ssrcss-wpgbih-StyledFigure e34k3c23\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21\"><span class=\"ssrcss-1exovz1-Placeholder e16icw910\"><img class=\"ssrcss-evoj7m-Image ee0ct7c0\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/640/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 800w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 976w\" alt=\"2px presentational grey line\" width=\"640\" height=\"2\" loading=\"lazy\"></span></div>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-dm4ypg-ComponentWrapper-HeadlineComponentWrapper e1xue1i89\" data-component=\"subheadline-block\">\r\n<h2 id=\"We-are-suffering\" class=\"ssrcss-y2fd7s-StyledHeading e1fj1fc10\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span role=\"text\">\'We are suffering\'</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\"><strong class=\"ssrcss-hmf8ql-BoldText e5tfeyi3\">Rajini Vaidyanathan, BBC South Asia correspondent in Colombo</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The streets of this usually bustling capital are much quieter now and Colombo has the feel of a city under lockdown. With fuel in short supply people have been urged to stay home where possible.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">But outside fuel stations is where you will find long queues. Members of the military guard the pumps, patrolling the forecourts - here petrol has become more precious than gold.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"piano-inline3\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Van driver Aziz has been in line for two days: \"We are suffering, we\'ve no lunch no breakfast, we\'ve just had water as we wait.\"</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The struggle for fuel is also accompanied by a struggle for food. With food inflation at 80% for the month of June, many Sri Lankans are skipping meals. Charity Unicef says more than two-thirds of the country has cut down on food since the start of the year.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Its spokesperson in Sri Lanka told the BBC that if outside help doesn\'t arrive soon to this island nation, there could be a humanitarian crisis in the coming months.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-18mjolk-ComponentWrapper e1xue1i810\" data-component=\"image-block\">\r\n<figure class=\"ssrcss-wpgbih-StyledFigure e34k3c23\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-ab5fd8-StyledFigureContainer e34k3c21\"><span class=\"ssrcss-1exovz1-Placeholder e16icw910\"><img class=\"ssrcss-evoj7m-Image ee0ct7c0\" src=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/640/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png\" srcset=\"https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/240/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 240w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/320/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 320w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 480w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/624/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 624w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/800/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 800w, https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/976/cpsprodpb/1226D/production/_105894347_grey_line-nc.png 976w\" alt=\"2px presentational grey line\" width=\"640\" height=\"2\" loading=\"lazy\"></span></div>\r\n</figure>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">BBC India business correspondent Archana Shulka says that while Sri Lanka has not completely ground to a halt yet, it is precariously close to seizing up.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Export-driven industries, such as textile and clothing, have been helped to keep going by the government as the economy needs to earn significant amounts of foreign currency.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">However, the fuel supplies needed to power machinery in these industries and to transport goods are also drying up now, our correspondent says.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The IT industry, which is still developing in the country, has also been heavily affected as firms face power cuts and internet outages.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">All of this has prompted concerns of a so-called \"brain drain\", with fears that large numbers of young professionals could leave the country.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">Last Thursday, an International Monetary Fund team concluded a fresh round of talks with Sri Lanka over a $3bn (&pound;2.5bn) bailout deal.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">While no agreement has been reached yet,&nbsp;<a class=\"ssrcss-k17ofw-InlineLink e1no5rhv0\" href=\"https://www.imf.org/en/News/Articles/2022/06/30/pr22242-imf-staff-concludes-visit-to-sri-lanka\">the team said in a statement</a>&nbsp;that it had made \"significant progress on defining a macroeconomic and structural policy package\".</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">It added that it had \"witnessed some of the hardships currently faced by the Sri Lankan people, especially the poor and vulnerable who are affected disproportionately by the crisis\".</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-uf6wea-RichTextComponentWrapper e1xue1i86\" data-component=\"text-block\">\r\n<div class=\"ssrcss-7uxr49-RichTextContainer e5tfeyi1\">\r\n<p class=\"ssrcss-1q0x1qg-Paragraph eq5iqo00\">The cash-strapped country has also sent officials to the major energy producers Russia and Qatar in an attempt to secure cheap oil supplies.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '04. 7. 2022 | 21:34', 1, 6);

